Example QFeatures object after processing

Source: R/data.R
feat3.Rd

feat3 is a small QFeatures object dataset can be is an example that tests QFeatures as it could routinely be used within a pipeline. Note that the 3 special cases of AssayLinks are present in this dataset:

  • One to one link: link between 1 parent and 1 child with one to one row mapping. E.g. "peptides" to "normpeptides"

  • One parent to multiple children: link between 1 parents and multiple children mapping. E.g. "peptides" to "normpeptides" and "proteins"

  • Multiple parents to one child: link between multiple parents and one child mapping. E.g. "psms1" and "psms2" to "psmsall"

feat3

Format

An object of class QFeatures of length 7.

Source

The pRolocdata package: http://bioconductor.org/packages/pRolocdata/

Details

Run plot(feat3) for an overview of the relationships

See also

See feat1 for other example and test data sets.

Examples


data("feat3")
plot(feat3)
